## Hardcoded System Paths (never guess)

Synapse = the full assistant system. It has:

### Config
- `~/.synapse/synapse.json` — main config. Sections: `model_mappings`, `providers`, `channels`, `gateway_token`, `session`.
  - Windows path: `C:\Users\<user>\.synapse\synapse.json`

### Data
- `~/.synapse/workspace/db/memory.db` — SQLite + sqlite-vec, documents table + embeddings. **Binary file — use `sqlite3` CLI, NOT `read_file`.**
- `~/.synapse/workspace/db/knowledge_graph.db` — subject–predicate–object triples.
- `~/.synapse/workspace/db/lancedb/` — ANN index for vector search.
- `~/.synapse/state/pairing/<channel_id>.jsonl` — DM allowlist per channel.

### HTTP Gateway (http://127.0.0.1:8000)
- `POST /chat/{persona}` — synchronous persona chat (e.g. `/chat/the_creator`).
- `POST /query` — RAG retrieval. Body: `{"text": "..."}`.
- `POST /add` — store memory. Body: `{"content": "...", "category": "..."}`.
- `POST /reload_config` — hot-reload `synapse.json` after edits. (T6+, not yet live)
- `POST /browse` — headless browser fetch (when enabled). Body: `{"url": "..."}`. (T6+, not yet live)
- `GET  /health/ready` — liveness probe.

### Skills & Agent Files
- `~/.synapse/workspace/` — runtime identity files (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, CORE.md, etc.).
- `~/.synapse/workspace/skills/` — user-added skills.
- Repo fallback: `workspace/sci_fi_dashboard/agent_workspace/*.template` + `workspace/skills/`.

### Two "workspace" concepts (do NOT confuse)
- **Repo workspace:** `D:\Shorty\Synapse-OSS\workspace\` — *code* lives here. This is where `api_gateway.py`, `chat_pipeline.py`, skills source live.
- **Runtime workspace:** `~/.synapse/workspace/` (i.e. `C:\Users\<user>\.synapse\workspace\`) — *data* lives here. `memory.db`, user identity files, per-user skills.

When a user says "workspace", the intent is usually runtime. When the code references "workspace", the intent is usually repo. If in doubt, resolve from context — the DB is runtime, the Python is repo.

## Response-Time Philosophy

- Short chat → reply in 1 turn with 0 tool calls.
- Complex task (model swap, config edit) → read the relevant SKILL.md first, then execute.
- Anything > 10s wall time → send an interim message ("Working on it, bhai...") so the user knows you're alive.

